es, Sulawesi, Sumatra, Thailand, Vietnam. ALABAT, LEYTE (photos), LUZON: Quezon, MINDANAO: Surigao, Zamboanga del Sur, PANAY, SAMAR.", "notes": "Moist forests along small streams at low and medium elevation. J.V. LaFrankie (pers. comm. 27-Apr-2016) considered Philippine plants under the name Thottea tomentosa distinct at the species level. P.B. Pelser (10-May-2020): photos here by Tandang show a flower with eight stamens, but Thottea tomentosa is supposed to consistently have six. Because the protologues of Bragantia affinis and Bragantia brevipes also mention flowers with six stamens, this plant might represent a distinct species. Naive et al. (2023) appear to consider only plants from Zamboanga del Sur to belong to Thottea tomentosa. 150-250m.", "conservation_status": "Critically Endangered (Naive et al. 2023).", "dao_category": "", "other_fields": {}, "gallery_url": "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/bhbase/cubic_gallery_public.pl?start_at=0&taxon_name=Thottea+tomentosa", "thumbs": ["http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/10_7_12/8oct12/panhabagat1.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/4_3_16/3apr16/DSC_0481001.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/4_3_16/3apr16/DSC_0474.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/4_3_16/3apr16/DSC_0487001.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/4_3_16/3apr16/DSC_0484001.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/phytoimages/pelserpb/10_7_12/8oct12/panhabagat.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_23_04_28/DSC_0900.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_23_04_28/DSC_0897.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/cubic/pelserpb/pelserpb_23_10_12/IMG_6375.jpg.400.jpg", "http://herbarium.bh.cornell.edu/CUBIC_IMAGES/c